Project Title
JobSentinel – Web-Based Job Fraud Detection & Trust System
Domain - Cybersecurity / Recruitment Technology
Methodology - Agile (Scrum Framework)
Tagline - “Your career’s first line of Defense.”

1. Project Vision
Vision Statement
To empower job seekers with a reliable, easy-to-use system that detects fraudulent job postings from any online source and builds trust through recruiter verification and community reporting.

2. Business Problem & Need
Problem Description
Fake job postings are increasingly circulated via:
•	WhatsApp groups
•	Telegram channels
•	Social media platforms
•	Fake recruiter websites
Once job descriptions are shared outside portals like LinkedIn or Naukri, users lose all protection.
Impact
•	Financial loss due to fake registration fees
•	Data theft (ID, resume, bank details)
•	Psychological stress and career setbacks
Proposed Solution
JobSentinel allows any job post from any source to be:
•	Analyzed for fraud risk
•	Verified by recruiters
•	Reviewed by community and admin



